DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Donor Cell Bone Marrow Assessment Percentage Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the value as a percentage of 100 related to the smallest units of living structure capable of independent existence, composed of a membrane-enclosed mass of protoplasm and containing a nucleus or nucleoid, from someone who gives blood to be used in another person and the tissue occupying the spaces of bone (bone marrow, which consists of blood vessel sinuses and a network of hematopoietic cells which give rise to the red cells, white cells, and megakaryocytes).
